Find customers who never placed an order.

SELECT *
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id 
WHERE o.order_id IS NULL;

I used a LEFT JOIN to keep all records from the customers table 
while looking for matching customer_id values in the orders table. 
If no matching order exists, the order columns are returned as NULL. 
Filtering for order_id IS NULL gives customers who have never placed an order.
